This last installment of the Tokimeki Memorial Girl's side series opens as tradition dictates with a tale, which this time brings us back to the origins of the game because it also refers to the first game and its legend.
First of all, the heroine and two young children were playing hide and seek. One of the little boys will eventually tell them a story:
&quot;The princess waiting in the church picked a primrose. It was the key to the fairies. Thinking of the person you love, you can join her.&quot;
